# =============================================================================
# KEY PATTERNS
# =============================================================================

1. INDEX.yaml in every major directory
   - Auto-generated index for quick lookup
   - Source of truth is the folder contents
   - Run sync script to regenerate

2. README.md in every folder
   - Explains folder purpose
   - Provides quick navigation
   - Documents conventions

3. Backup naming convention
   - {FILENAME}.backup.{TIMESTAMP}
   - Examples:
     - STATE.yaml.backup.1770341176
     - STATE.yaml.backup.20260204_093350

4. YAML structure patterns
   - meta: at top with version, timestamp
   - Sections with clear headers
   - Consistent indentation (2 spaces)

5. Task folder structure
   - Folder-per-task pattern
   - Required files: task.md, THOUGHTS.md, DECISIONS.md, RESULTS.md
   - Optional files: LEARNINGS.md, ASSUMPTIONS.md, PLAN.md
   - Subfolders: timeline/, subtasks/, artifacts/

6. Goal/Plan/Task hierarchy
   - goals/ -> plans/ (via symlinks)
   - plans/ -> tasks/ (via symlinks)
   - Creates navigable hierarchy

7. .docs/ folders
   - AI-managed documentation
   - System guides and specifications
   - Auto-generated from patterns
